title: Saints Tame Tigers All Over the Field
text:
Saints Tame Tigers All Over the Field 
By Norman Seawright III October 10, 2015 Updated Oct 10, 2015 at 10:54 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) -- The St. Scholastica (CSS) football team handed Iowa Wesleyan its sixth loss of the season, while remaining undefeated in Upper Midwest Athletic Conference (UMAC) play. 
The Saints capitalized on Mike Mensing's passing game and Alex Mangan's forced fumble and blocked punt return to establish a strong lead over the Tigers in the first half, winning 41-7.
